  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `.claude/agents/researcher.md` to confirm invocation protocol and knowledge-repository-first lookup order.</step>
    <step order="2">Invoke the `researcher` subagent with the prompt: "Investigate whether `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Testing` (or an equivalent Microsoft-shipped companion to `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` v10.3.0) exists as a STABLE NuGet package providing `IChatClient` streaming mocks consuming `IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;`. Apply these decision criteria from design.md §5.1: (a) stable, not preview; (b) provides IChatClient streaming mocks specifically; (c) referenced in Microsoft samples or Microsoft.Extensions.AI test code; (d) integrates with NSubstitute/Moq without conflict. Return: explicit verdict (use Microsoft / hand-roll / escalate) + evidence (NuGet versions, Microsoft Learn URLs, GitHub sample paths)."</step>
    <step order="3">Receive subagent response. Validate it explicitly maps each of the 4 §5.1 criteria (✅ / ⚠️ / ❌ for each).</step>
    <step order="4">Write `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/decisions/D-01-async-enumerable-helper.md` with sections: Context (1 paragraph), Verdict (1 sentence), §5.1 Criteria Mapping (table), Evidence (bullets with URLs), Implication for P1.B1 (1 paragraph specifying which approach the to-be-generated task should take).</step>
    <step order="5">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md` with completion + the verdict summary line.</step>
  </steps>

