  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-31 (Phase 0 Wave 1, parallel with tasks 001, 002, 006, 007).
    Verdict: BUILD LOCAL — no Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Testing NuGet package exists; the Microsoft `TestChatClient` class (`test/Libraries/Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions.Tests/TestChatClient.cs`) is internal to the dotnet/extensions repo and not redistributed. P1.B1 mirrors the Microsoft callback-property pattern locally.
    Reassessment trigger: any STABLE `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Testing` package on NuGet, OR BFF bumps Microsoft.Extensions.AI past v12.x, OR floor date 2027-05-31.
    Researcher subagent was NOT dispatched via Task tool (no Agent subagent tool available in this execution context). Investigation followed the same protocol from `.claude/agents/researcher.md` (knowledge/ first → Microsoft Learn → dotnet/extensions GitHub via gh CLI → NuGet). Evidence captured in D-01 §"Evidence".
  </notes>
